nl_ps: John spoke to Mary at four o'clock. ## And Bill did at five o'clock.
fol_ps: SpokeTo(john, mary, fourOclock) ## exists x. (Bill(x) & Time(x, 5) & DidAt(x, 5))
nl_h: Bill spoke to Mary at five o'clock.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. exists z. (Bill(x) & Mary(y) & Five(z) & Oclock(z) & SpokeAt(x, y, z))
label: e

nl_ps: John has spoken to Mary. ## Bill is going to.
fol_ps: HasSpoken(john, mary) ## Going(bill) & To(bill)
nl_h: Bill will speak to Mary.
label: e

nl_ps: John spoke to Mary on Monday. ## Bill didn't.
fol_ps: SpokeTo(john, mary, monday) ## not Bill(x)
nl_h: Bill spoke to Mary on Monday.
label: c

nl_ps: Has John spoken to Mary? ## Bill has.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Person(x) & Person(y) & SpokenTo(x, y)) ## Has(bill)
nl_h: Bill has spoken to Mary.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & Mary(y) & SpokenTo(x, y))
label: e

nl_ps: John has spoken to Mary. ## The students have too.
fol_ps: HasSpoken(john, mary) ## exists x. (Student(x) & Too(x))
nl_h: The students have spoken to Mary.
fol_h: exists x.exists y. (Student(x) & Mary(y) & SpokenTo(x, y))
label: e

nl_ps: John is going to Paris by car, and the students by train.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (John(x) & Paris(y) & GoesByCar(x, y)) & (Students(x) & Train(y) & GoesByTrain(x, y))
nl_h: The students are going to Paris by train.
label: e

nl_ps: John had his paper accepted. ## Bill doesn't know why.
fol_ps: HadPaperAccepted(john) ## not (exists x. (Person(x) & Knows(x, y) & Why(y)))
nl_h: Bill knows why John had his paper accepted.
label: c

nl_ps: John spoke to Mary. ## And to Sue.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Person(x) & Person(y) & SpokenTo(x, y)) ## exists x. (Person(x) & Name(x, "Sue") & Person(x))
nl_h: John spoke to Sue.
label: e

nl_ps: John spoke to Mary. ## On Friday.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Person(x) & Person(y) & SpokenTo(x, y)) ## Friday(x)
nl_h: John spoke to Mary on Friday.
label: e

nl_ps: John spoke to Mary on Thursday. ## And on Friday.
fol_ps: SpokeTo(john, mary, thursday) ## exists x. (Friday(x) & On(x) & Friday(x))
nl_h: John spoke to Mary on Friday.
label: e

nl_ps: Twenty men work in the Sales Department. ## But only one woman.
fol_ps: exists x. (Man(x) & WorksInSalesDepartment(x)) ## exists x. (Woman(x) & not exists y. (Woman(y) & not Woman(z) & Man(z) & DifferentFrom(y, z)))
nl_h: Two women work in the Sales Department.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. (Woman(x) & Woman(y) & WorkInSalesDepartment(x) & WorkInSalesDepartment(y))
label: c

nl_ps: John wants to know how many men work part time. ## And women.
fol_ps: WantsToKnow(John, NumberOfPartTimeMen) ## exists x. (Woman(x))
nl_h: John wants to know how many women work part time.
label: e

nl_ps: John wants to know how many men work part time, and which.
fol_ps: exists x. (Man(x) & Part(x) & Time(x) & WantsToKnow(John, x))
nl_h: John wants to know which men work part time.
fol_h: exists x. (Man(x) & Part(x) & Time(x) & WantsToKnow(John, x))
label: e

nl_ps: Bill spoke to everyone that John did. ## John spoke to Mary.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & John(y) & SpokeTo(x, y)) ## exists x. exists y. (Person(x) & Person(y) & SpokenTo(x, y))
nl_h: Bill spoke to Mary.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & Mary(y) & SpokeTo(x, y))
label: e

nl_ps: Bill spoke to everyone that John did. ## Bill spoke to Mary.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & John(y) & SpokeTo(x, y)) ## exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & Mary(y) & SpokeTo(x, y))
nl_h: John spoke to Mary.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. (Person(x) & Person(y) & SpokenTo(x, y))
label: n

nl_ps: John needed to buy a car, and Bill did.
fol_ps: exists x.exists y. (NeededToBuyCar(x) & NeededToBuyCar(y) & (John(x) & Bill(y)))
nl_h: Bill bought a car.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. (Bill(x) & Car(y) & Bought(x, y))
label: n

nl_ps: Smith claimed he had costed his proposal and so did Jones.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Smith(x) & Jones(y) & (Costed(x) & Proposal(x) & CostedProposal(y)))
nl_h: Jones claimed he had costed his own proposal.
label: e

nl_ps: Smith claimed he had costed his proposal and so did Jones.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Smith(x) & Jones(y) & (Costed(x) & Proposal(x) & CostedProposal(y)))
nl_h: Jones claimed he had costed Smith's proposal.
label: e

nl_ps: Smith claimed he had costed his proposal and so did Jones.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Smith(x) & Jones(y) & (Costed(x) & Proposal(x) & CostedProposal(y)))
nl_h: Jones claimed Smith had costed Smith's proposal.
label: e

nl_ps: Smith claimed he had costed his proposal and so did Jones.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Smith(x) & Jones(y) & (Costed(x) & Proposal(x) & CostedProposal(y)))
nl_h: Jones claimed Smith had costed Jones' proposal.
label: n

nl_ps: John is a man and Mary is a woman. ## John represents his company and so does Mary.
fol_ps: exists x. exists y. (Man(x) & Woman(y) & (John(x) & Mary(y))) ## exists x.exists y. (John(x) & Mary(y) & (Represents(x) & Company(x) & RepresentsCompany(y)))
nl_h: Mary represents her own company.
label: e

nl_ps: Bill suggested to Frank's boss that they should go to the meeting together, and Carl to Alan's wife.
fol_ps: exists x.exists y.exists z. (Bill(x) & Frank(y) & Alan(z) & (SuggestedTo(x, y, z) & not SuggestedTo(x, z, y)))
nl_h: If it was suggested that Bill and Frank should go together, it was suggested that Carl and Alan should go together.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. exists z. exists w. (Suggested(x, y, z) & Suggested(y, w, z) & (Bill(x) & Frank(y) & Carl(w) & Alan(z)))
label: e

nl_ps: Bill suggested to Frank's boss that they should go to the meeting together, and Carl to Alan's wife.
fol_ps: exists x.exists y.exists z. (Bill(x) & Frank(y) & Alan(z) & (SuggestedTo(x, y, z) & not SuggestedTo(x, z, y)))
nl_h: If it was suggested that Bill and Frank's boss should go together, it was suggested that Carl and Alan's wife should go together.
fol_h: exists x. exists y. exists z. exists w. (Suggested(x, y, z) & Boss(y) & Bill(y) & Frank(y) & Suggested(x, w, z) & Boss(z) & Carl(z) & Alan(z) & Suggested(x, w, z))
label: e

nl_ps: A lawyer signed every report, and so did an auditor. ## That is, there was one lawyer who signed all the reports.
fol_ps: exists x.exists y. (Lawyer(x) & Auditor(y) & (Signed(x) & Report(x) & SignedReport(y))) ## exists x. (Lawyer(x) & SignedAllReports(x))
nl_h: There was one auditor who signed all the reports.
label: e
